        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 12:43PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1242 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Heavener, moving northeast at 70 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Greenwood...                      Arkola...
Patterson...                      Huntington...
Crossroads...                     Liberty...
Witcherville...                   Dayton...
Milltown...                       Wister...
Midland...                        Heavener...
Howe...                           Hartford...
Burnville...                      Hodgen...
Mansfield...                      Poteau...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
